<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 13 at 8:01AM CDT until June 13 at 8:15AM CDT by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 815 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN FANNIN COUNTY...
At 801 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southeast of
Dodd City, or 12 miles southeast of Bonham, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Honey Grove, Ladonia, Pecan Gap, Windom, Bug Tussle, Allens Chapel,
Allens Point, Dial and Gober.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection stay inside a sturdy structure and keep away from
windows.</instruction>
